\begin_inset Formula $\Hilb$
\end_inset

 (constructed over the uncountable and uncomputable complex numbers 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathbb{C}$
\end_inset

), we will consider variants constructed over finite fields
\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset


\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand cite
key "HansonOrtizSabryEtAl2015,DQT2014,geometry2013"

\end_inset

.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Instead of real-valued probability measures producing results in the uncountable
 and uncomputable interval 
\begin_inset Formula $[0,1]$
\end_inset

