 In more detail, a probability space consists of a 
\emph on
sample space
\emph default
 
\begin_inset Formula $\Omega$
\end_inset

, a space of 
\emph on
events
\emph default

\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset


\begin_inset Formula $\events$
\end_inset

, and a 
\emph on
probability measure
\emph default

\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset


\begin_inset Formula $\pmeas$
\end_inset

