 events.
 It is useful to think that this probability measure is completely induced
 by the two coins in question and their characteristics in the sense that
 each pair of coins induces a measure, and each measure must correspond
 to some pair of coins.
 The measure above is induced by two coins such that the first coin is twice
 as likely to land tails up than heads up and the second coin is double-headed.
 
